    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n5848" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">λίσσομαι</span></b>  (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">λιτή</span>), ipf. (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐ</span>)(<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">λ</span>)<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">λίσσετο</span>, iter. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">λισσέσκετο</span>, aor. 1 <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐλλισάμην</span>, imp. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">λίσαι</span>,
          aor. 2 <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐλιτόμην</span>, inf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">λιτέσθαι</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">pray, beseech</span> with
          prayer; abs., <i><span class="en">Il. 22.91</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 2.68</span></i>, and <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τινὰ
            εὐχῇσι, εὐχωλῇσι λιτῆσί τε, Ζηνός</span>, ‘in the name of Zeus’;
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πρός, ὑπέρ τινος, γούνων</span> (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">λαβών, ἁψάμενος</span>), etc.; foll. by inf.,
          sometimes <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὅπως</span> or <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἵνα,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Od. 3.19</span></i>, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">
            237</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 8.344</span></i>; with two
          accusatives, <i><span class="en">Od. 2.210</span></i>, cf. <i><span class="en">Od. 4.347</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
